13/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Volker Ruehe, the head of the German Federal Parliament's Foreign Affairs Committee, said the conduct of free and fair elections in Albania would be crucial to Tirana's EU integration process.
Ruehe met with Prime Minister Fatos Nano in Tirana on Tuesday (12 October).
He said all political parties, as well as international institutions, must consider the 2005 elections legitimate.
In other news, Albanian and Bulgarian officials met on Tuesday to discuss bilateral co-operation in the judiciary.
They agreed such co-operation would help each accelerate their respective accession processes.
(ATA - 12/10/04)
